A lone raven, a feathered silhouette against the bruised twilight sky, croaked a mournful lament. Deep within a tangled thicket, where shadows danced and the earth hummed with unseen life, lay a fragment, a whisper from the past. This fragment, a string of genetic code, held a silent narrative, a story written in an alphabet of bases.  It was discovered near a crumbling stone circle, its purpose lost to the mists of ages.
